# SEO Implementation Walkthrough

**Goal**: Increase organic ranking and local map visibility for Bakudan Ramen.

## Summary of Changes
Based on the implementation plan, we have transformed the single-page local redesign into a robust, multi-page structure optimized for Local SEO. We used the new, text-based HTML menu design as the foundation.

### 1. Created Specific Location Pages
Instead of a single `/location/` page, we have generated three new pages in the `/locations/` directory:
- [the-rim.html](file:///Users/hoangle/Project/Antigravity/Bakudan-SEO/locations/the-rim.html)
- [stone-oak.html](file:///Users/hoangle/Project/Antigravity/Bakudan-SEO/locations/stone-oak.html)
- [bandera.html](file:///Users/hoangle/Project/Antigravity/Bakudan-SEO/locations/bandera.html)

### 2. Implemented LocalSchema (JSON-LD)
We injected precise Schema.org structured data into the `<head>` of each new location page. This code acts as a direct line to search engines, explicitly identifying the page as a Restaurant and providing exact details.

**Example: The Rim Schema Implementation**
```html
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Restaurant",
  "name": "Bakudan Ramen - The Rim",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "streetAddress": "17619 La Cantera Pkwy UNIT 208",
    "addressLocality": "San Antonio",
    "addressRegion": "TX",
    "postalCode": "78257"
  },
  "telephone": "+12102578080",
  // ... including specific hours and ratings
}
</script>
```

### 3. Updated Navigation Links
We modified the template's navigation bar so the "Location" link now points correctly to the new architecture. For example, on the Rim page, it points to `/locations/the-rim.html`.

## Verification Results
- **Files Created**: Verified the presence of all three `.html` files in the `locations/` directory.
